From: Til Kaiser <mail@tk154.de>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: ipq5332: add NSS fabric clocks to nsscc

Add the GCC-provided NSS fabric clocks used by the IPQ5332 NSSCC PM clock
setup to the nsscc node.

Besides the existing NSSCC and NSSNOC inputs, IPQ5332 also needs the
NSSNOC-to-SNOC and SNOC-to-NSSNOC fabric clocks to be described as nsscc
clock inputs so they can be requested by name and kept enabled while NSSCC
is active.

Signed-off-by: Til Kaiser <mail@tk154.de>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5332.dtsi | 24 ++++++++++++++++++++----
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5332.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/ipq5332.dtsi
@@ -993,7 +993,27 @@
 				 <&pcs0 1>,
 				 <&pcs1 0>,
 				 <&pcs1 1>,
-				 <&xo_board>;
+				 <&xo_board>,
+				 <&gcc GCC_NSSCC_CLK>,
+				 <&gcc GCC_NSSNOC_NSSCC_CLK>,
+				 <&gcc GCC_NSSNOC_SNOC_CLK>,
+				 <&gcc GCC_NSSNOC_SNOC_1_CLK>,
+				 <&gcc GCC_SNOC_NSSNOC_CLK>,
+				 <&gcc GCC_SNOC_NSSNOC_1_CLK>;
+			clock-names = "cmn_pll_nss_clk_200m",
+				      "cmn_pll_nss_clk_300m",
+				      "gcc_gpll0_out_aux",
+				      "uniphy0_rx",
+				      "uniphy0_tx",
+				      "uniphy1_rx",
+				      "uniphy1_tx",
+				      "xo",
+				      "bus",
+				      "nssnoc",
+				      "nssnoc_snoc",
+				      "nssnoc_snoc_1",
+				      "snoc_nssnoc",
+				      "snoc_nssnoc_1";
 			#clock-cells = <1>;
 			#reset-cells = <1>;
 			#interconnect-cells = <1>;
